        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3632562362" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11937164386094501855"> <b>3 Stars</b><br/><br/><b>Overall Opinion: </b>This was a cute story that had me smiling and laughing a few times. I liked the wholesomely good connection between these two and how they both loved each other. It did get a to be a little too much of the mushy stuff at times, but I barreled through. It did feel long because it felt like it took me a long time to read. It flowed well for the most part, but I think just a lot happens in the book to where it didn’t feel like closure was in sight. While it ended on a good </span>
  <span id="freeText11937164386094501855" style="display:none"> <b>3 Stars</b><br /><br /><b>Overall Opinion: </b>This was a cute story that had me smiling and laughing a few times. I liked the wholesomely good connection between these two and how they both loved each other. It did get a to be a little too much of the mushy stuff at times, but I barreled through. It did feel long because it felt like it took me a long time to read. It flowed well for the most part, but I think just a lot happens in the book to where it didn’t feel like closure was in sight. While it ended on a good note, it felt like an odd time to end. To be completely honest, I think the last trial of drama they face wasn’t all that necessary and could’ve been edited out easily to make a more complete feeling ending. Overall, I didn’t hate it or anything, but I also didn’t love it....it was just okay.<br /><br /><b>Brief Summary of the Storyline: </b> This is Elly and Will’s story. Will is a wanderer trying to survive. Once he is let go from his position at the sawmill in a small Georgia town, he hears about the town’s crazy widow that put an add in the paper for a husband. He meets a very pregnant Elly with her two small sons and soon realizes that he can easily make a home working her late husband’s property and that she isn’t so crazy after all. They become fast friends and decide to get married after all, and then stronger feelings start to develop. There is some past baggage they have to work through, some sweet scenes with Elle’s kids, the start of WWII, and some town drama...and they get a HEA ending. <br /><br /><b>Point Of View (POV):</b> This alternated between focusing mainly on Elly and Will (and some side characters) in 3rd person narrative.<br /><br /><b>Overall Pace of Story: </b>Alright. I never skimmed but this felt long, and it kinda was @ 432 pages in my kindle app.<br /><br /><b>Instalove:</b>No, they become friends first then it turns into more.<br /><br /><b>H (Hero) rating:</b> 4 stars. Will. I liked him. I liked how he craved to be loved and how he loved in return.<br /><br /><b>h (heroine) rating:</b> 4 stars. Elly. I liked her. I liked how she appreciated the small things and loved her family.<br /><br /><b>Sadness level: </b>Low, no tissues needed<br /><br /><b>Push/Pull:</b> Yes, but mild <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[The H pushes away at one point and I’d say they both pursue the relationship  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br /><b>Heat level:</b> Low. They have some non-descriptive scenes -- but not very many and not so much it takes away from the story.<br /><br /><b>Descriptive sex:</b> Not really. Not quite fade to black but not really descriptive either.<br /><br /><b>OW (Other Woman)/OM (Other Man) drama:</b> Kind of <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[ There is a OW that the H doesn’t like (and says so) but she pursues him strongly several times and causes some drama for the couple <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br /><b>Sex scene with OW or OM:</b> No<br /><br /><b>Cheating: </b> No<br /><br /><b>Separation:</b> Yes, but only physically <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[They are separated for a while (~year?) <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[while he is away for war <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>, but there was no mention or suggestion of other partners during this time.  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br /><b>Possible Triggers: </b>Yes <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[The H is an orphan/poverty (on page), the H murdered a whore to protect friend and was incarcerated for 5 years (off page), the h was married and had children with dead husband, h was abused emotionally and suggestion of physically as a child (off page), and loss of a friend (off page) <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br /><b>Closure: </b> This ends in a good place with a HEA ending <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[they’re still married and she’s pregnant <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br /><b>Safety:</b> This one should be <u>Safe</u> for most safety gang readers<br /><a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[<br />- <b>Does Not</b> have cheating<br />- <b>Does Not</b> have a descriptive sex scene with OW/OM<br />- <b> Does </b> have the H pushing the h away (minimal)<br />- <b> Does</b> have a (physical) separation between the h and H<br />- <b> Does Not</b> have abuse by mc<br />- <b>Does </b> have a HEA ending <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span></span>
