<div id="review_1469605431" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1469605431" />
    <a title="Preeti ♥︎ Her Bookshelves" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/32506772-preeti-her-bookshelves"><img alt="Preeti ♥︎ Her Bookshelves" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1467833378p2/32506772.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1469605431?book_show_action=true">Mar 27, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Preeti ♥︎ Her Bookshelves" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Preeti ♥︎ Her Bookshelves" href="/user/show/32506772-preeti-her-bookshelves">Preeti ♥︎ Her Bookshelves</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780425229286" href="/book/show/6346632-morning-glory">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32506772-preeti-her-bookshelves?shelf=love-the-intimacy-n-interplay">love-the-intimacy-n-interplay</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32506772-preeti-her-bookshelves?shelf=separation-long-ish">separation-long-ish</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32506772-preeti-her-bookshelves?shelf=husband-hunting">husband-hunting</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32506772-preeti-her-bookshelves?shelf=h-widow">h-widow</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32506772-preeti-her-bookshelves?shelf=ow-wannabe-or-cover">ow-wannabe-or-cover</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32506772-preeti-her-bookshelves?shelf=p-soldier-spy">p-soldier-spy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32506772-preeti-her-bookshelves?shelf=moc-arrnged-forcd-mino">moc-arrnged-forcd-mino</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32506772-preeti-her-bookshelves?shelf=outcast-blaksheep-misfit-disgrace">outcast-blaksheep-misfit-disgrace</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32506772-preeti-her-bookshelves?shelf=grieving-a-spouse-or-love">grieving-a-spouse-or-love</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32506772-preeti-her-bookshelves?shelf=skim-sigh-skip">skim-sigh-skip</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1469605431" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9099027418519334852">There are so many great and detailed reviews so I won’t even try.<br/>Just some rambling.<br/><br/>Will is a H to die for. Honorable and humane even after all the deprivations of his life. The h started out as a loving, giving Pollyanna but began withholding before long and annoyed the hell out of me. <br/>Maybe I loved Will so much that I resented her not caring for him unreservedly. <br/>His love and caring felt wholesome and unselfish, while hers was more about what he could do for her. But still their together momen</span>
  <span id="freeText9099027418519334852" style="display:none">There are so many great and detailed reviews so I won’t even try.<br />Just some rambling.<br /><br />Will is a H to die for. Honorable and humane even after all the deprivations of his life. The h started out as a loving, giving Pollyanna but began withholding before long and annoyed the hell out of me. <br />Maybe I loved Will so much that I resented her not caring for him unreservedly. <br />His love and caring felt wholesome and unselfish, while hers was more about what he could do for her. But still their together moments were adorable and heart-tugging. The kids were so real and winsome.<br /><br />The wartime subplot was overlong, the letters-chapters sweet but monotonous after a while. The H perhaps needed it to redeem his own worth as a person, and to become a valued and respectable citizen of society.<br />The ow-villain drama was icky, maybe necessary (to cover all bases) but predictable.<br /><br />One thing I dislike is when hs force Hs (and vice versa) to do something that is totally out of their comfort zone – like being solely responsible for her childbirth. If it’s an emergency then it’s a different matter, but here the h saw how uncomfortable, even fearful he was about it but she laid down the ultimatum and told him to either her way or the highway – literally. First she ‘lures’ him into feeling at home for the first time in his life and then she cracks the whip. Maybe she dint quite realize it but her ultimatum was incredibly cruel.<br /><br />And ….the bees were so real I could actually hear them lazily buzzing around the sunny orchards and I would have loved some of that honey for my muffins too!<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="9099027418519334852" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


