<div id="review_3197455859" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3197455859" />
    <a title="Jultri" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11762474-jultri"><img alt="Jultri" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1514197791p2/11762474.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3197455859?book_show_action=true">May 05, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jultri" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jultri" href="/user/show/11762474-jultri">Jultri</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/11568333-morning-glory">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11762474-jultri?shelf=marriage-of-convenience">marriage-of-convenience</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11762474-jultri?shelf=tortured-hero">tortured-hero</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11762474-jultri?shelf=widow">widow</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11762474-jultri?shelf=traumatised-heroine">traumatised-heroine</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11762474-jultri?shelf=world-war-ii">world-war-ii</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3197455859" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17762152561681779137">4.25/5. Well this is a very unique slow-burn love story between two lonely and socially ostracised people, who agreed to a marriage of convenience out of desperation. She&apos;s a struggling widowed mother of two young ones and another in the oven. He is a newly released convicted murderer who answers her unconventional advertisement for a helper/husband to assist with the many physical tasks required to run her farm. <br/><br/>Ejected from yet another job due to his criminal past, Will is just grateful for fo</span>
  <span id="freeText17762152561681779137" style="display:none">4.25/5. Well this is a very unique slow-burn love story between two lonely and socially ostracised people, who agreed to a marriage of convenience out of desperation. She's a struggling widowed mother of two young ones and another in the oven. He is a newly released convicted murderer who answers her unconventional advertisement for a helper/husband to assist with the many physical tasks required to run her farm. <br /><br />Ejected from yet another job due to his criminal past, Will is just grateful for food to fill his gnawing belly and not to be looked at with distrust by another human being. Used to back-breaking hard work, he is more than willing and able to take on any task required for him to stay employed at this grossly neglected farm. If marriage is part of the deal, he'll take that too because it offers greater permanency. <br /><br /><i>She was almost as sorry-looking as her place, and pregnant to boot. He needed a dry bed, but preferably not one with her in it.</i> <br /><br />Eleanor grew up in an oppressive and abusive household, initially forbidden to interact with the outside world, and then when she was finally allowed this interaction through compulsory school attendance, she discovered this world to be unkind and judgemental - much like home. Only her husband had ever shown her goodness and affection and with him gone, her only link to society had disappeared with him. But being practical, she knows with her baby due within months that she and the kids will need the help of an outsider. <br /><br />Two people who grew up devoid of love and tenderness in their lives now bound together out of their common need for survival. Gradually, trust and affection bloom between them and both grow in confidence as individuals and in their interactions with others.<br /><br /><i><br />And at long, long last the loneliness of Will Parker’s life stopped hurting. He thought her name over and over—Elly... Elly—a benediction, as the kiss deepened, firmer, fuller, but still with a certain reserve—two people schooled to reject the possibility of miracles now forced to change their beliefs.<br /><br /><br />The sting hit his eyelids and he hung his head because nobody had prepared him for this, nobody had said, When it happens you’ll be resurrected. All that you were you will not be. All that you weren’t, you are.</i><br /><br /><br />Lovely story with sweet and vulnerable protagonists you just want to hug and protect. Their loneliness, their distrust in mankind, their raw needs to be loved, to be cared for, to be trusted by another - all depicted so well by the author. The setting, America just before and during WWII, is fascinating in its details of how life changed for the everyday American. I've read many WWII books, mostly from a European perspective, but never read about the impact on US soil. Will's interactions and growing fondness for Elly's boys are endearing. <br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="17762152561681779137" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


